\frac{1-\bar{z}}{(1-z)(1-\bar{z})}=\frac{1-\bar{z}}{2(1-Re(z))}.
z \in\mathbb{C}\setminus \{1\}
|z|=1.
\frac{1}{1-z}=\frac{1-\bar{z}}{(1-z)(1-\bar{z})}=\frac{1-\bar{z}}{1-z-\bar{z}+z\bar{z}}=\frac{1-\bar{z}}{1-2\Re{z}+|z|^2},
\frac{1-\bar{z}}{(1-z)(1-\bar{z})}=\frac{1-\bar{z}}{2(1-\Re(z))}
Re(z) = \frac{z + \bar{z}}{2}
z=x+iy
\{1-(x+iy)\}\{1-(x-iy)\}=2(1-x)
(1-x)^2-(iy)^2=2-2x
x^2+y^2=1\implies \mid z\mid =1
